This is... Okay, all right.

01:00:56.960 --> 01:00:58.039
Sophie, come on.

01:00:58.040 --> 01:00:59.879
Let's just take a breath here, okay?

01:00:59.880 --> 01:01:02.639
I know you're feeling
something that is magical

01:01:02.640 --> 01:01:04.079
and clearly exciting to you,

01:01:04.080 --> 01:01:07.868
but if you think about it logically,
literally for one second...

01:01:17.680 --> 01:01:19.466
Is this weird for you now?

01:01:26.760 --> 01:01:30.039
Does anybody remember any
of those fun icebreaker games

01:01:30.040 --> 01:01:32.679
that kids do at summer camp...

01:01:32.680 --> 01:01:34.181
[LAUGHING]

01:01:34.760 --> 01:01:39.479
Spin the bottle or seven minutes
in heaven or something...

01:01:39.480 --> 01:01:41.559
Anyhow, we just thought it was time

01:01:41.560 --> 01:01:43.439
that the four of us sit down

01:01:43.440 --> 01:01:45.359
and get to know each
other a little bit.

01:01:45.360 --> 01:01:47.159
You want to get to know each other?

01:01:47.160 --> 01:01:48.879
Hi, Sophie.

01:01:48.880 --> 01:01:50.620
Hi.

01:01:52.240 --> 01:01:54.399
Okay. Um...

01:01:54.400 --> 01:01:56.319
Let's get to know each other.

01:01:56.320 --> 01:01:58.879
Why don't you tell us the truth
of what's really going on?

01:01:58.880 --> 01:01:59.999
The truth?

01:02:00.000 --> 01:02:02.799
Yeah, that you basically have
been pretending to be me,

01:02:02.800 --> 01:02:04.359
acting like I don't exist

01:02:04.360 --> 01:02:06.959
even though you knew I
was here the whole time.

01:02:06.960 --> 01:02:09.959
Ethan, I wasn't
pretending to be anyone.

01:02:09.960 --> 01:02:12.224
I was just being myself.

01:02:12.400 --> 01:02:14.359
You knew about me, right?

01:02:14.360 --> 01:02:16.279
Did he mention me
to you at any point?

01:02:16.280 --> 01:02:18.270
Not until this morning.

01:02:19.000 --> 01:02:20.559
All right. Maybe all of us

01:02:20.560 --> 01:02:23.439
were doing a little
pretending this weekend.

01:02:23.440 --> 01:02:25.430
It's not a big deal.

01:02:26.000 --> 01:02:28.039
I really like your shoes.

01:02:28.040 --> 01:02:30.622
Oh, thank you.

01:02:31.720 --> 01:02:34.279
I really like your hair
pinned back like that.

01:02:34.280 --> 01:02:35.799
It's super cute.

01:02:35.800 --> 01:02:40.439
I'm sorry. I still am not
buying that you are real.

01:02:40.440 --> 01:02:43.199
ETHAN 2: Ethan, I'm sitting here,

01:02:43.200 --> 01:02:44.679
you're looking at me sitting here.

01:02:44.680 --> 01:02:45.999
I'm real.

01:02:46.000 --> 01:02:47.879
You're sitting across from me, right?

01:02:47.880 --> 01:02:49.359
I'm looking at you sitting there,

01:02:49.360 --> 01:02:53.581
so by your logic maybe
you're not real.

01:02:53.720 --> 01:02:56.109
That doesn't make any sense.

01:02:57.120 --> 01:02:58.319
I'm starving.

01:02:58.320 --> 01:02:59.879
Ethan, why don't you
clean yourself up

01:02:59.880 --> 01:03:01.745
and we'll all have a little dinner.

01:03:11.280 --> 01:03:12.941
There.

01:03:14.280 --> 01:03:17.919
So, anybody interested in
going on a hike tomorrow?

01:03:17.920 --> 01:03:19.959
I've been wanting to do that
ever since we got here.

01:03:19.960 --> 01:03:21.439
I would love that.

01:03:21.440 --> 01:03:22.959
All right.

01:03:22.960 --> 01:03:25.119
Tonight though,
I'm thinking game night.

01:03:25.120 --> 01:03:26.479
All right.

01:03:26.480 --> 01:03:29.239
Okay, maybe you're real,
but can we admit

01:03:29.240 --> 01:03:31.399
this isn't some normal dinner party?

01:03:31.400 --> 01:03:33.159
Ethan, you're looking
a little uncomfortable.

01:03:33.160 --> 01:03:34.359
Can I help you with something?

01:03:34.360 --> 01:03:36.239
Okay, so according to you,

01:03:36.240 --> 01:03:38.359
this is just some average weekend.

01:03:38.360 --> 01:03:39.919
We all go home tomorrow,

01:03:39.920 --> 01:03:43.708
and you don't need any further
explanation than that?

01:03:44.040 --> 01:03:46.159
Sometimes these things just happen.

01:03:46.160 --> 01:03:48.742
Yeah, that's right. They do.

01:03:51.080 --> 01:03:52.706
I don't buy it.

01:03:52.840 --> 01:03:53.919
ETHAN 2: All right.

01:03:53.920 --> 01:03:56.719
One time I read this article
on cosmic occurrences.

01:03:56.720 --> 01:03:58.839
I wish I still had it...
You would love it.

01:03:58.840 --> 01:04:01.559
And it basically says
that aberrations happen.

01:04:01.560 --> 01:04:03.559
You can drive yourself nuts
trying to derive meaning

01:04:03.560 --> 01:04:06.381
from things that have no
meaning to begin with.

01:04:06.640 --> 01:04:07.879
That's so interesting.

01:04:07.880 --> 01:04:09.506
ETHAN 2: It is, isn't it?

01:04:09.760 --> 01:04:11.239
It's not that interesting.

01:04:11.240 --> 01:04:12.679
Let me think of an
little example for you,

01:04:12.680 --> 01:04:16.159
something right up your alley.

01:04:16.160 --> 01:04:17.879
Um...

01:04:17.880 --> 01:04:19.679
Let's say you buy a gorilla.

01:04:19.680 --> 01:04:21.227
Excuse me?

01:04:21.320 --> 01:04:23.439
Let's say you buy a gorilla, Ethan.

01:04:23.440 --> 01:04:25.679
You can't buy a gorilla.

01:04:25.680 --> 01:04:28.639
I know that, it was for the story.

01:04:28.640 --> 01:04:31.825
But fine, let's say you
buy an aardvark, okay?

01:04:33.400 --> 01:04:36.119
You take that aardvark,
you put him in a dark room.

01:04:36.120 --> 01:04:38.799
A minute later you flip that
switch, the lights come on.

01:04:38.800 --> 01:04:40.399
Now we all know how
electricity works,

01:04:40.400 --> 01:04:43.519
but for him it's a miracle.

01:04:43.520 --> 01:04:44.879
Magic happened...

01:04:44.880 --> 01:04:46.839
That previously dark
room is now illuminated

01:04:46.840 --> 01:04:49.229
with possibilities he's
never seen before...

01:04:49.440 --> 01:04:50.519
And what does he do?

01:04:50.520 --> 01:04:53.227
Does he ruin it by
questioning how or why?

01:04:54.080 --> 01:04:57.311
No. He enjoys it.

01:04:58.280 --> 01:04:59.599
Huh.

01:04:59.600 --> 01:05:01.909
Well, I'm not an aardvark.

01:05:02.200 --> 01:05:04.509
And I am not a gorilla.

01:05:08.400 --> 01:05:10.425
Don't worry about it. I got it.

01:05:15.280 --> 01:05:16.781
[SIGHS]

01:05:20.120 --> 01:05:21.621
Hmm.

01:05:21.640 --> 01:05:23.266
There's a little bit left.

01:05:23.560 --> 01:05:25.107
Should we finish it?

01:05:39.840 --> 01:05:42.359
[SIGHS] This is quite the situation.

01:05:42.360 --> 01:05:44.146
You can say that again.

01:05:44.800 --> 01:05:48.782
Has Ethan... I mean your Ethan...

01:05:48.880 --> 01:05:51.599
Have you guys talked about anything

01:05:51.600 --> 01:05:54.039
or has he said anything
to you at all?

01:05:54.040 --> 01:05:55.587
Like What?

01:05:55.600 --> 01:05:58.879
Well, Ethan... My Ethan
and I, we've discussed it.

01:05:58.880 --> 01:06:01.679
Like he knew when I was
going to go in the house

01:06:01.680 --> 01:06:04.399
and I knew when he
was going to and...

01:06:04.400 --> 01:06:06.629
You shared your experiences.

01:06:07.040 --> 01:06:08.719
Yeah, for the most part.

01:06:08.720 --> 01:06:12.827
And you want to know if we
shared our experiences also.

01:06:13.840 --> 01:06:15.990
Guess I'm just curious.

01:06:16.040 --> 01:06:17.826
I can see that.

01:06:19.400 --> 01:06:21.743
You know what I'm curious about?

01:06:22.560 --> 01:06:25.119
Are you more concerned
with the experiences

01:06:25.120 --> 01:06:27.599
that me and your Ethan shared

01:06:27.600 --> 01:06:29.879
or are you more concerned
with what I know

01:06:29.880 --> 01:06:32.860
about the experiences that
you and my Ethan shared?

01:06:34.480 --> 01:06:35.879
Seems to me you care a lot more

01:06:35.880 --> 01:06:38.508
about one of those
scenarios than the other.

01:06:41.480 --> 01:06:43.505
Are you going to give that back?

01:06:52.440 --> 01:06:54.479
[SIGHS]

01:06:54.480 --> 01:06:57.799
I say for the sake of
the super fun evening

01:06:57.800 --> 01:07:00.839
we're about to have,
let's keep it simple

01:07:00.840 --> 01:07:02.119
and keep our cheery dispositions

01:07:02.120 --> 01:07:05.679
and I'll keep
complimenting your shoes.

01:07:05.680 --> 01:07:06.799
And you can keep pretending

01:07:06.800 --> 01:07:08.679
that you like the way
I pin my hair back,

01:07:08.680 --> 01:07:11.911
and we'll just have a good
time and see what happens.

01:07:17.120 --> 01:07:19.987
On second thought, do you mind
taking care of those dishes?

01:07:24.800 --> 01:07:27.064
You still haven't told
me where you're from.

01:07:27.080 --> 01:07:28.879
Are we still doing this?

01:07:28.880 --> 01:07:30.839
Are we going to compare
lists of women, too?

01:07:30.840 --> 01:07:32.679
You know, I'm starting
to piece this all together

01:07:32.680 --> 01:07:34.466
and see it for what it is.

01:07:34.760 --> 01:07:37.149
You're trying to sabotage
my relationship.

01:07:37.400 --> 01:07:40.039
Ethan, from what I understand
about your relationships,

01:07:40.040 --> 01:07:43.749
you should be well versed
in the art of self-sabotage.

01:07:44.480 --> 01:07:46.159
The purpose of tonight
is not to engage

01:07:46.160 --> 01:07:48.389
in some warped
competition between us,

01:07:48.440 --> 01:07:50.199
at least not on my end.

01:07:50.200 --> 01:07:52.270
It wouldn't really be fair.

01:07:52.360 --> 01:07:54.510
Yeah? Why is that?

01:07:56.760 --> 01:07:58.705
Haven't you figured it out yet?

01:08:00.400 --> 01:08:01.559
ETHAN 2: It's kings.

01:08:01.560 --> 01:08:03.879
It's kings or it's aces
is what's going on.

01:08:03.880 --> 01:08:05.679
There's something going on.

01:08:05.680 --> 01:08:08.547
SOPHIE: Why don't you worry
about your own cards.

01:08:09.040 --> 01:08:10.839
I don't even know why
we're continuing right now.

01:08:10.840 --> 01:08:13.308
I basically know every
card you're holding.

01:08:13.600 --> 01:08:15.359
Are you saying that I have a tell?

01:08:15.360 --> 01:08:16.919
You have big tells.

01:08:16.920 --> 01:08:19.158
[WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY]

01:08:19.160 --> 01:08:20.799
You want to know what your tell is?

01:08:20.800 --> 01:08:22.759
I want to know what you think it is.

01:08:22.760 --> 01:08:26.189
You have a very consistent
albeit very cute

01:08:26.240 --> 01:08:30.104
Sophie shoulder shrug that
looks a little bit like this.

01:08:31.600 --> 01:08:33.828
Oh! Do you do the shrug?

01:08:34.040 --> 01:08:35.359
Uh, excuse me. Don't talk to her.

01:08:35.359 --> 01:08:36.599
She's dead. She folded.

01:08:36.600 --> 01:08:38.078
It's just you and me now.

01:08:38.080 --> 01:08:39.198
You did the shoulder shrug.

01:08:39.200 --> 01:08:40.599
You obviously have a good hand.

01:08:40.600 --> 01:08:43.078
It's like a high pair or
maybe even three of a kind.

01:08:43.080 --> 01:08:44.279
Fucking raise this shit, man.

01:08:44.279 --> 01:08:46.020
You only live once.

01:08:46.040 --> 01:08:47.871
Okay. I'll raise.

01:08:48.200 --> 01:08:49.599
Now I know you have the confidence.

01:08:49.600 --> 01:08:50.759
I have a shit hand.

01:08:50.760 --> 01:08:52.038
I'm folding. Look at that.

01:08:52.040 --> 01:08:53.279
Jesus, are you kidding me?

01:08:53.279 --> 01:08:55.919
- What?
- You're right.

01:08:55.920 --> 01:08:58.118
- Pair of aces.
- Ooh!

01:08:58.120 --> 01:08:59.679
Nailed it, nailed it.

01:08:59.680 --> 01:09:01.679
I knew you had the aces.

01:09:01.680 --> 01:09:03.959
Dude, by the way, you're getting
very good at this game...

01:09:03.960 --> 01:09:05.078
Almost too good.

01:09:05.080 --> 01:09:08.060
I'm beginning to think this
is like one long Sophie con.

01:09:09.640 --> 01:09:11.319
He clearly just let you win.

01:09:11.319 --> 01:09:13.359
Yes, Ethan. Obviously he let me win.

01:09:13.359 --> 01:09:14.439
Come on, guys.

01:09:14.439 --> 01:09:16.590
This is supposed to just
be a friendly game.

01:09:17.640 --> 01:09:19.399
You're not being very
fun to play with.

01:09:19.399 --> 01:09:22.759
The reason he's not being fun
is because he's not even playing.

01:09:22.760 --> 01:09:24.078
Ethan, if you want to win the game,

01:09:24.080 --> 01:09:25.999
you've got to play some hands, okay?

01:09:26.000 --> 01:09:27.626
That's just how it works.

01:09:30.000 --> 01:09:32.069
All right. Fine. I'll play.

01:09:33.240 --> 01:09:34.559
Deal me in. You and me.

01:09:34.560 --> 01:09:35.679
Come on.

01:09:35.680 --> 01:09:37.670
You want to play one on...

01:09:38.040 --> 01:09:40.399
Okay. All right. That's the spirit.

01:09:40.399 --> 01:09:41.919
Come on, buddy.
Let's get in the game.

01:09:41.920 --> 01:09:43.466
Let's go.

01:09:46.479 --> 01:09:47.981
Mmm-hmm.

01:09:50.640 --> 01:09:51.919
All right.

01:09:51.920 --> 01:09:54.104
How many cards do you want?

01:09:54.279 --> 01:09:55.359
I'm fine with what I have.

01:09:55.360 --> 01:09:57.146
Thank you very much.

01:09:57.360 --> 01:09:58.679
Sticking with what you have.

01:09:58.680 --> 01:10:00.199
All right. I'll stick
with what I have, too.

01:10:00.200 --> 01:10:01.781
What's your move?

01:10:04.800 --> 01:10:06.301
I'm all in.

01:10:06.520 --> 01:10:07.999
Oh!

01:10:08.000 --> 01:10:10.239
All in, bold move!

01:10:10.240 --> 01:10:13.061
But you've got to be impulsive
sometimes. I really like it.

01:10:13.080 --> 01:10:14.159
All right, so you're all in,

01:10:14.160 --> 01:10:18.142
and now I've got to figure
out what is your tell.

01:10:18.240 --> 01:10:19.919
You've got that restless
leg thing going on

01:10:19.920 --> 01:10:21.639
but I think it's just nerves.

01:10:21.640 --> 01:10:23.399
You've been chewing on
the lower lip a little bit,

01:10:23.400 --> 01:10:25.679
but I get ulcers in there, too,

01:10:25.680 --> 01:10:27.919
so maybe that's just what that is.

01:10:27.920 --> 01:10:29.199
So weird lip...

01:10:29.200 --> 01:10:31.319
Oh!

01:10:31.320 --> 01:10:34.027
Oh, shit! Of course. There it is.

01:10:35.360 --> 01:10:38.639
The guy who has nothing
and he knows it.

01:10:38.640 --> 01:10:41.507
Sorry, buddy, but I've got
to call you on this one.

01:10:42.040 --> 01:10:43.701
What you got?

01:10:46.600 --> 01:10:48.340
Whatever.

01:10:48.440 --> 01:10:52.381
You have nothing and I
win with an ace high.

01:10:52.560 --> 01:10:53.879
Sorry about that, man.

01:10:53.880 --> 01:10:57.190
It's fun playing with you, but you've
got to work on your bluffing skills.

01:10:57.760 --> 01:10:58.879
You win.

01:10:58.880 --> 01:11:00.359
You're an amazing liar.

01:11:00.360 --> 01:11:02.559
Congratulations on being a shithead.

01:11:02.560 --> 01:11:05.119
- Whoa!
- Ethan, Jesus. Calm down.

01:11:05.120 --> 01:11:06.919
Hey, wait a minute, wait a minute.

01:11:06.920 --> 01:11:08.399
I don't want to take
all the credit here.

01:11:08.400 --> 01:11:11.346
You're a pretty decent
liar yourself, right?

01:11:16.320 --> 01:11:18.119
What are you talking about?

01:11:18.120 --> 01:11:19.599
Do you want to tell her or should I?

01:11:19.600 --> 01:11:20.759
Is this necessary?

01:11:20.760 --> 01:11:22.959
I think it's important that
Sophie knows what's going on.

01:11:22.960 --> 01:11:24.079
We're all friends here, right?

01:11:24.080 --> 01:11:26.599
Uh, would everybody just tell
me what we're talking about?

01:11:26.600 --> 01:11:27.879
What happened?

01:11:27.880 --> 01:11:29.039
It's nothing.

01:11:29.040 --> 01:11:30.871
ETHAN 2: All right, look,

01:11:31.200 --> 01:11:34.639
Ethan was a little suspicious that
something was going on between us,

01:11:34.640 --> 01:11:37.479
so he decided to try and
figure it out for himself.

01:11:37.480 --> 01:11:39.359
It was actually kind
of a brilliant move.

01:11:39.360 --> 01:11:40.839
He didn't go to the grocery store.

01:11:40.840 --> 01:11:43.439
He ended up sneaking
into the guest house,

01:11:43.440 --> 01:11:45.479
and in a strange twist of events,

01:11:45.480 --> 01:11:49.079
he pretended to be me,

01:11:49.080 --> 01:11:52.759
so you actually slept
with Ethan instead of me.

01:11:52.760 --> 01:11:56.039
I can't fucking pretend
to be you... I am me.

01:11:56.040 --> 01:11:58.119
You... What the fuck
are you talking about?

01:11:58.120 --> 01:12:00.439
Just shut up! Sophie, please.

01:12:00.440 --> 01:12:02.430
That was you yesterday?

01:12:03.600 --> 01:12:05.079
Sweetheart...

01:12:05.080 --> 01:12:08.199
ETHAN 2: Basically, first he betrayed

01:12:08.200 --> 01:12:09.879
you by sleeping with someone else

01:12:09.880 --> 01:12:14.908
and then he kind of betrayed
you by sleeping with you.

01:12:15.480 --> 01:12:19.701
Sorry, guys. I didn't want
to make like a thing here.

01:12:20.120 --> 01:12:22.919
If you guys need some
space or something.

01:12:22.920 --> 01:12:26.119
If you want to like take the
guest house, you'd be welcome.

01:12:26.120 --> 01:12:27.860
I'm not going anywhere.

01:12:30.720 --> 01:12:33.348
No, I want you to leave.

01:12:44.040 --> 01:12:46.679
<i>THERAPIST:
...if not, leave a detailed message</i>

01:12:46.680 --> 01:12:47.879
<i>and I will return your call.</i>

01:12:47.880 --> 01:12:49.279
[BEEPS]

01:12:49.280 --> 01:12:50.599
Hey. It's Ethan.

01:12:50.600 --> 01:12:52.599
